    "Finally, we conclude our survey in Sect. 9.",
    "A point cloud is a set of geometric points situated on the surfaces of 3D objects in Euclidean space.",
    "These points are typically captured using 3D sensors like LiDAR, laser scanners, structured light scanners, or Time-of-Flight (ToF) RGB-D cameras.",
    "A point p i in a point cloud P can be represented by its x, y, and z Cartesian coordinates, denoted as",
    ", where N is the number of points in P."
